ce:section.ce:para:
CDs facilitate the loading of nanodrugs on their surface due to their large specific surface area. Catalyzed by transition metal atoms or ions loaded by CDs, the overexpressed hydrogen peroxide in tumors undergoes Fenton reaction, which generates hydroxyl radicals that are toxic to cells and inhibit them. Simultaneous bursting or enhancement of CDs fluorescence is used to detect GSH depletion and improve the tumor environment (
                           Fig. 20
                           ). Easily modified CDs can improve the inherent poor targeting of CDT and reduce cytotoxicity.
